About the Business

The story. Our profile. The 411. You get the idea. Ok, we're gonna keep this quick. Because exceptional quality at lightning fast speed is what we're all about. Blaze Pizza. Head food guy, Executive Chef Bradford Kent (aka "The Pizza Whisperer"). Fresh, made-from-scratch dough. Healthful, artisanal ingredients on the assembly line. Inventive to classic. You decide. Blazing hot oven + dedicated pizzasmith + 180 seconds = fast-fire'd, perfectly crisp perfection. Sound good? Enjoy the rest of your day.…

    There is no better build-your-own-pizza place.  Blaze is THE standard against which all others are measured, for good reason.

    Quality: 5
    Value: 5
    Service: 5
    Ambiance: 5

    We've been going to Blaze in Davis for years, and their staff have done an AWESOME job adapting to COVID.  I am talking everyone properly wearing their masks every time we go in, social distancing, tons of hand sanitizer - the works.

    Blaze has not only really delicious ingredients and pre-made options, but an unbeatable value-for-quality for their customized BYOP.  You can pile every single ingredient onto one pie and the price doesn't go up.  You can do half-and-half pizzas.  You can ask them to do weird things to pizzas, like put stuff on halfway through, and they accommodate the request.

    I really just don't have anything bad to say about Blaze.  They're the best.

    Typical blaze- got the crust, toppings oven buffet style. Menu now includes pricing options for different  number of toppings on build your own pizza.

    We went at around 8pm , with not that much people but it took almost an hour. Some of it is agreed that it is a little overstuffed and the people ahead of us took advantage of the take two deal with pesto on the crust and salad that was running out , but overall was still a long wait. They went light on the pizza which was good for crispness but lacked for meat and made it a bit dry.

    Either way, blaze is pretty consistent overall so theres not much to say. It's a build your own pizza place where they have signature options and options to customize everything- sauce, toppings and drizzles.
    The place has adequate seating and pretty nice lighting, it's a bit partnered with ikes sandwiches in location.

    I got half art lover and half pesto chicken ( wish there was more pesto), you can sub different toppings but its $1 extra to add more toppings.

    Blaze Pizza is, generally speaking, a great restaurant chain. Cheap but quality food, & friendly service.

    This particular location is cheap, the service is good, but the food is consistently bad. I've ordered from here 4 times & every single time my order has been either incorrect or burned to a crisp.

    Yes, burned. Like charred cardboard burned. I'm gluten intolerant & I always order the cauliflower crust. I use cauliflower crust at home when I bake my own pizzas. It never ever turns out as brittle & inedible as Blaze's. Sure, it cooks differently compared to traditional dough. But it shouldn't be so tough that it's virtually impossible to enjoy.

    I gave them the benefit of the doubt because I figured it was just a newbie screw up or something. Hey, we're human. We make mistakes. But the poor food quality is consistent here. Won't be back anymore. Bummed because Blaze is a fun spot.

  • Leanne M.

    Elite '2021

    Davis, CA
    33
    70
    331
    9/3/2019
    3 photos

    My only issue with Blaze is their 'keto' crust pizza.

    I'm giving them 4 stars because I honestly believe their build your own is the best way to eat pizza around Davis.
    With a huge range of toppings it's pretty friendly to anybody who could walk in the door, they offer gluten free crust and will always ask if you need a change of gloves which is great for someone who's celiac.

    They offer vegan cheese and vegan meatballs as well as a huge array of veggie toppings, olives jalepenos, chopped garlic, roasted garlic cloves, onion, mushrooms, a seasonal veggie - I've seen it be squash or Brussels (you'll be amazed how good they are on pizza) peppers, arugula to finish - there's a tonne of options here!

    They offer four sauces, classic and spicy marinara, cream sauce and garlic pesto. - LOVE the garlic pesto

    A variety of meats - sausage, pepperoni, ham, bacon, meatballs, chicken

    And plenty of cheese - highly recommend getting both the fresh mozzarella and the shredded. They also offer gorgonzola, feta, ricotta and Parmesan  

    I'm sure I'm missing some toppings and I'm sure they change from time to time too! But I think you'll gather that you won't be short of options here!

    And then there's the Keto Crust - I did a really detailed review of this for my blog myfairfitness. com so if you're curious on my full thoughts on ingredients to after effects feel free to check it out! I think it's too much to include on a review of blaze as a whole. But what I will say is if you're strict keto the ingredients aren't friendly, if you're just trying to stay low on carbs it's fine. The texture is ok if it's anyway over cooked the cauliflower in it turns bitter, you can definitely make a better Keto Crust at home. It's crispy and a little smaller, not worth the extra dollars in my opinion... and the effects it had on my stomach were not good. It's nice they do the option but they could have done it better.
